commands:
  (global) --quiet / -q  Suppress info logs (auto-enabled in robot mode)
  (global) --verbose/-v  Enable debug logs (overrides auto-quiet)
  Tip: `--robot-docs=<topic>` is normalized to `robot-docs <topic>`; globals can appear before/after subcommands.
  cass search <query> [OPTIONS]
    --agent A         Filter by agent (e.g. codex, claude_code, gemini, opencode, antigravity; run `cass capabilities --json | jq .connectors` for the full 23-connector inventory)
    --workspace W     Filter by workspace path
    --limit N         Max results (default: 0 = no limit)
    --offset N        Pagination offset (default: 0)
    --json | --robot  JSON output for automation
    --fields F1,F2    Select specific fields in hits (reduces token usage)
                      Presets: minimal (path,line,agent), summary (+title,score), provenance (source_id,origin_kind,origin_host)
                      Fields: score,agent,workspace,workspace_original,source_path,snippet,content,title,created_at,line_number,match_type,source_id,origin_kind,origin_host
    --max-content-length N  Truncate content/snippet/title to N chars (UTF-8 safe, adds '...')
                            Adds *_truncated: true indicator for each truncated field
    --today           Filter to today only
    --yesterday       Filter to yesterday only
    --week            Filter to last 7 days
    --days N          Filter to last N days
    --since DATE      Filter from date (YYYY-MM-DD)
    --until DATE      Filter to date (YYYY-MM-DD)
    --aggregate F1,F2 Server-side aggregation by fields (agent,workspace,date,match_type)
                      Returns buckets with counts. Reduces tokens by ~99% for overview queries
    --mode lexical|semantic|hybrid  Search mode (default: hybrid; hybrid fails open to lexical when semantic assets are unavailable)
    --robot-meta     Include readiness, requested/realized mode, semantic refinement, fallback tier/reason, cursor, and timing metadata
  cass pack <query> [--robot] [--max-tokens N] [--limit N]
    Build a deterministic, cited answer pack for agent handoffs without external summarization.
    --sessions-from FILE|-  Restrict evidence to newline-delimited session paths; '-' reads stdin.
    --fields minimal|summary|all,F1,F2  Select top-level pack fields for JSON/TOON output.
    --max-sessions N  Cap how many sessions can contribute evidence to the pack.
    --max-evidence N  Cap cited evidence items selected into the pack.
    --max-excerpt-chars N  Bound each excerpt before token estimation.
    --freshness-policy prefer-recent|strict|allow-stale  Evidence freshness policy.
    --freshness-window-seconds N  Freshness window used for stale-evidence warnings and strict filtering.
    --require-evidence  Return a JSON error envelope instead of an empty successful pack.
    --explain-selection  Include score components and omission diagnostics for audits.
    Output includes health, freshness, privacy, evidence, omitted, and warnings fields.
  cass swarm status --json [--repo PATH] [--include-evidence]
    Read-only swarm operations snapshot over Beads, Agent Mail metadata, git, rch/build pressure, cass readiness, and proof evidence.
    Reports ready/in-progress/blocked beads, stale candidates, reservations, active agents, proof gaps, and safe next actions.
    Stale detection is advisory only; status never claims, reopens, force-releases, runs builds, rewrites files, or deletes data.
  cass swarm work-packet --json [--bead ID]
    Advisory packet for one possible work slice: readiness, suggested reservations, coordination copy, verification commands, and closeout checklist.
    It does not update Beads, send Agent Mail, create file reservations, or run the proof commands.
  cass swarm lint --json [--bead ID]
    Read-only protocol lint for missing start/closeout mail, unacked messages, stale reservations, bead-status mismatches, and proof gaps.
  cass swarm dependency-drift --json
    Read-only sibling dependency sentinel over Cargo.toml pins, optional local checkout HEAD/dirty state, strict validation commands, and release-risk recommendations.
    It never fetches remotes, edits manifests, updates Beads, sends Agent Mail, runs builds, deletes files, or changes git state.
  cass stats [--json] [--data-dir DIR]
  cass triage [--json] [--stale-threshold N] [--data-dir DIR]
    One-shot agent preflight: readiness, next_command, recommended_commands, docs, schemas, workflows, and recoveries.
    Aliases: ready, preflight.
  cass status [--json] [--stale-threshold N] [--data-dir DIR]
  cass diag [--json] [--verbose] [--data-dir DIR]
  cass sessions [--workspace DIR] [--current] [--limit N] [--since WHEN] [--json]
  cass view <path> [-n LINE] [-C CONTEXT] [--json]
  cass index [--full] [--watch] [--json] [--robot-trace-ingest] [--data-dir DIR]
                    In --json mode, NDJSON events stream on stderr:
                      {event:started|phase|progress|completed|error, ...}
                    Tune with --progress-interval-ms N (250..60000, default 2000),
                    disable with --no-progress-events or CASS_INDEX_NO_PROGRESS_EVENTS=1.
                    Add --robot-trace-ingest for per-batch wall_ms, batch_msgs, and duplicate-lookup counters on stderr.
                    From another shell: `cass status --json` shows live progress.
  cass tui [--once] [--data-dir DIR] [--reset-state] [--asciicast FILE]
  cass capabilities [--json]   First-stop self-description: workflows, mistake recoveries, commands, flags, exit codes, env vars, limits.
  cass robot-docs <topic>
  cass --robot-help
  cass health [--json]             Minimal readiness probe (<50ms, exit 0=healthy, 1=unhealthy).
  cass doctor [--json] [--fix]     Legacy spelling: --json realizes read-only check; --fix realizes safe-auto-run.
                    doctor JSON includes source_inventory; missing upstream provider files are
                    source coverage/prune-risk warnings, not proof that archived cass rows are lost.
                    raw_mirror defines/verifies the content-addressed raw session evidence layout.
                    raw_mirror.policy states the privacy boundary: default robot JSON, logs,
                    support bundles, HTML exports, and Pages exports do not include raw bytes or exact source paths.
  cass doctor check --json          Explicit read-only doctor v2 truth surface.
  cass doctor repair --dry-run --json
                    Preview a fingerprinted repair plan without mutating filesystem or archive state.
  cass doctor repair --yes --plan-fingerprint <fp> --json
                    Apply only the inspected plan whose fingerprint exactly matches the dry-run.
  cass doctor --fix --json          Legacy safe-auto-run; safe derived repairs only, with receipts for every mutation.
  cass doctor --fix --force-rebuild --json
                    Requests derived rebuild inside safe-auto-run; never bypasses archive/source authority gates.
                    Robots should read introspect.response_schemas doctor-* contracts and branch on
                    err.kind/status/operation_outcome.kind/outcome_kind/asset_class/risk_level/fallback_mode.
  cass doctor --ls --json           List per-run artifact dirs under <data_dir>/doctor/runs/ (read-only).
  cass doctor --undo <RUN_ID> --json
                    Restore byte-identically from the per-run backups; `latest` alias supported. Refuses on tamper.
  cass doctor --robot-triage --json One-shot agent triage: summary, findings, recommended_command in one envelope.
  cass doctor --diff [<REF>|<A>..<B>] --json
                    Drift detection (`<REF>` mode) or run-to-run plan comparison (`<A>..<B>` mode). Read-only.
  cass doctor --gc-before <ISO> --yes --json
                    Quarantine doctor runs older than the cutoff. Never deletes (per AGENTS.md RULE NUMBER 1).
  cass doctor --watch --watch-interval-ms <N> --watch-iterations <N> --json
                    Long-running JSONL monitor; emits one `kind: watch-tick` event per poll. SIGINT exits 130.
  cass doctor --explain <RUN_ID> --json
                    Single envelope with run manifest + every recorded action + flattened band timeline.
  cass doctor --emit-capabilities --json
                    Self-describe: detectors[], fixers[], exit_codes[], data_paths[], env_vars[].
  cass robot-docs doctor             Paste-ready agent handbook for the doctor surface.
  cass introspect [--json]         Full API schema: commands, arguments, response_schemas (alphabetical).
  cass api-version [--json]        Show crate_version + api_version + contract_version.
  cass state [--json]              Alias of `cass status` (index/db/rebuild/semantic readiness).
  cass models status [--json]      Semantic model acquisition + cache state.
  cass models install [--from-file DIR] [--model minilm]  Download + install the MiniLM embedder.
  cass models remove [--model NAME]  Remove an installed semantic model from disk.
  cass models verify [--json]      Per-file SHA-256 verification of the installed model.
  cass models check-update [--json]  Compare installed revision against the pinned registry revision.
  cass models backfill             Re-embed conversations against a newly acquired model.
  cass expand <path> --line N [-C CONTEXT] [--json]  Show messages around a specific line in a session.
  cass resume <path> [--shell]     Resolve a session path into its native-harness resume command.
  cass timeline [--since DATE] [--until DATE] [--json]  Activity timeline over a time range.
  cass mirror prune [--older-than 90d] [--max-size 100GB] [--keep-tag important] [--apply] [--json]  Plan or apply raw-mirror retention with an audit log.
  cass context <path> [--json]     Find related sessions for a given source path.
  cass export <path> [--format markdown] [--output FILE]  Export a conversation to markdown / other formats.
  cass export-html <path> [--output-dir DIR] [--json]  Self-contained HTML export (optional encryption).
  cass pages [--export-only DIR] [--verify PATH] [--agents A1,A2]  Encrypted searchable archive for static hosting.
  cass sources [agents list|exclude|include] [setup|list|sync] [--json]  Manage remote sources + agent exclusions.
  cass swarm [status|work-packet|lint] --json  Read-only shared-repo operations guidance; complements Beads, Agent Mail, rch, and cass pack.
  cass analytics [status|tokens|tools|models|rebuild|validate] [--json]  Token / tool / model analytics.
  cass import [...]                Import conversation data from external sources.
  cass daemon [...]                Run the semantic model daemon (Unix only).
  cass completions <shell>         Emit shell completion script for bash | zsh | fish | powershell.
  cass man                         Emit man page (roff) for the cass binary.
